ct everyone to die in the lava, so with that being said I am gonna tell you how to whoop his butt without cheating =). First you must get rid of ANY and I do mean ANY flurries or adds, because you will need all attention on Vymmn for he is not easy, after you have killed all roamers work your way into the pit be careful though the pit is slippery and you will fall to his feet. Go to the back of his cave and shrink everyone, have your MT shoot arrows at Vymmn for a long period of time to get all his agro without doing much dmg this turns Vymmn's attention away from everyone. Now get buffed up and med up this part has to be fast so that no more roamers come by (one add of a flurry and you are a dead raiding party), ok now your all buffed and everyone is shrunk. There is a little ledge as you are looking out of the cave on your left, thats where the clerics should be it is close to Vymmn, but with shrink and on on that ledge he cannot hit your clerics with the AE which is how you win this fight. Now the MT runs in and the CH cycle starts, let him have agro for a min or so, then send the rest of the melee in on Vymmn's left side AND DO NOT GET BEHIND HIM FOR YOU WILL BE COME LAVA DINNER. Now everyone pushes Vymmn into the wall most of the time he will warp up there. This is a good thing cause now your clerics will not get hit by the AE (remember that little ledge), anyways now he is in a cornor, and remember rogues on these big dragons you can backstab from there side if you are right behind the hind legs, so you dont lose you DPS from not being behind them. Now the only way to beat Vymmn is to have MASSIVE DPS, this will be a long and terrible fight as his ae sends you flying into a wall then you have to run back up to him and the MT has to get agro again.....but that is the simple way of doing it, and all the other main dragons are 10 times easier then him all you have to do is hide your clerics, and make sure you have some alt healers for the other melee's for the main CH cycle group will be concentrating on the MT the whole time....Ohhh ya one other thing unless you want your first cleric to bite the dust make sure you have a pali LoH the MT for the first heal, cause the min a cleric hits that CH on the mob before the MT has main agro you can say goodbye to your first cleric, just a little fyi for ya. Well my time has been to long as it is I know alot about NToV if anyone has questions catch me in game and I will be glad to hook you up. Have a nice day everyone =) <p><br>Alfe Tsunammi 60th Assassin<br>Dangelec Blackheart 53rd Heretic<br>Brint 49th Cleric<br>Loci Linkdeadly 35th Shaman<TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD>
